@startuml Bus Station Management System - Network Topology
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFBFC
skinparam roundcorner 8
skinparam rectangleBorderColor #37474F

title Figure 2: Network Topology Diagram\n**Bus Station Management System**\n(Hierarchical Star)

' Central hub - single soft blue
rectangle "**Central Office / Data Center**\n\nApplication Server(s)\nDatabase Server(s)\nLoad Balancer\nFirewall" as HUB #7986CB {
  rectangle "BSMS Core" as CORE #9FA8DA
}

' Stations - same blue, lighter
rectangle "**Station A**\n(Ticketing Counters\nKiosks\nLAN)" as SA #B0BEC5
rectangle "**Station B**\n(Ticketing Counters\nKiosks\nLAN)" as SB #B0BEC5
rectangle "**Station C**\n(Ticketing Counters\nKiosks\nLAN)" as SC #B0BEC5
rectangle "**Station D**\n(Ticketing Counters\nKiosks\nLAN)" as SD #B0BEC5

' Mobile / remote - soft grey-blue
rectangle "**Mobile Users**\n(Passengers, Drivers)\n4G / Wi-Fi" as MOB #90A4AE
rectangle "**Remote Staff**\n(VPN)" as REM #90A4AE

' Connections - neutral
SA -[#546E7A]-> HUB : Fiber / Broadband\nDedicated Link
SB -[#546E7A]-> HUB : Fiber / Broadband\nDedicated Link
SC -[#546E7A]-> HUB : Fiber / Broadband\nDedicated Link
SD -[#546E7A]-> HUB : Fiber / Broadband\nDedicated Link
MOB -[#78909C,dashed]-> HUB : Internet\n(HTTPS / TLS)
REM -[#78909C,dashed]-> HUB : VPN\n(HTTPS)

note bottom of HUB
  **Central Hub**
  Single point of management
  and policy enforcement.
  Faults at one station do not
  bring down the core system.
end note

note as N1
  **Topology:** Hierarchical Star
  **Primary:** Fiber / Broadband / Wi-Fi
  **Secondary:** 4G/LTE for mobile
  **Security:** TLS, VPN for remote
end note

@enduml
